######## We start with the code 
######## https://github.com/AlexeyStaroletov/AxialAlgebras/blob/master/3gen/DataJordanHalf.g
######## We want to find alpha = (a,b), gamma = (a,c) and beta = (b,c) such that 
######## 1) alpha, beta, gamma are not equal to 1. 
######## 2) Moreover, (x_a(b),x_a(c))=1 when x_a(b) is not equal to x_a(c).

xb:=(2*ab - alp*a - b)/(alp-1);
xc:=(2*ac - gam*a - c)/(gam-1);

xb*Gram*xc;
######## gap> (-alp*gam-bet+2*phi)/(-alp*gam+alp+gam-1)
